data.value:
verse 1:
Hei hyvä haltija heilauta taikasauvaa
Tai noitaruhtinatar, hoida, vihreää ihmejuomaa
Ei kaniinia hatusta, ei enempää suolaa
Voisiko joku tämän kerran toiveeni toteuttaa

chorus:
Abrakadabra, tän täytyy toimia
Abrakadabra, ala rakastaa minua

verse 2:
Ne lepakonkynnet, ja liskonkeiton syön
Kuin nöyrä noviisi loitsuja luen tän yön
Näkyykö valoa kristallipallossa
Vai piinaanko ruumistani turhissa unelmissa

bridge:
Selasin Sudenpentujen käsikirjan ja Pikku Jättiläisen
Joo suutelen sammakon viimeisen katseesta yhden naisen

verse 1:
Hello good fairy wave a magic wand
Or witch princess, treat, green wonder potion
No rabbit in the hat, no more salt
Could someone make my wish come true for once?

chorus:
Abracadabra, this must work
Abracadabra, start loving me

verse 2:
I'll eat those bat claws and lizard soup
Like a humble novice I recite spells tonight
Can you see the light in the crystal ball
Or do I torture my body in vain dreams

bridge:
I looked through the Scout's Handbook and the information book for young people
Yeah, I'll kiss the last frog, for the look of one woman
Tornion Lappian muusikot - Abrakadabra (alkuperäinen esittäjä Mikko Kuustonen)

Miksasin koulutehtävänä ammattilaismuusikoiden Abrakadabra kappaletta ja ajattelin pystyväni samaan. Tuntui turhalta nauhoittaa sama kappale, joten tein oman, jossa on vielä löyhästi kuultavista ei-kopiosuojattuja ominaisuuksia Abrakadabrasta.

Verse 1:
Hello, good fairy waving her wand,
or witch princess with her wonder potion,
no rabbit in the hat or salt,
just wishing my wish would come true once.

Chorus:
Abracadabra, this must work,
Abracadabraz, start loving me.

Verse 2:
Eating bat claws, lizard soup,
reciting spells tonight,
seeing light in the crystal ball,
torturing my body in vain dreams.

Bridge:
Looking through my scout's handbook,
information book for young people,
Kiss the last frog for look of one woman.

Kohtaus 1:
Hei, hyvä keijus heiluttelemassa taikasauvaansa, 
tai noitanprinsessa ihmejuomallaan, 
ei kaninhattua tai suolaa, 
vain toivoen toiveeni toteutuvan kerran.

Kertosäe: 
Abracadabra, tämän pitäisi toimia, 
Abracadabraz, ala rakastamaan minua.

Kohtaus 2:
Syömässä lintujen kynsiä, liskojen keittoa, 
loitsien lukemista tänä iltana, 
valon näkemistä kristallipallosta, 
turhaan pilaamalla unia. 

Sillan:
Katselemaan väijyjäni käsikirjaa, 
nuorisolle tarkoitettua tietokirjaa, 
suudella viimeinen sammakko saadaksesi yhden naisen muodon.

1. What Mila Smith (born 2009, likes KoreaPop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics. Only about lyrics:
-Wow, this song is so magical! I can feel the power of the abracadabra behind the words. It's like the good fairy or witch princess are speaking right to me, trying to make my wish come true.

2. What Paul Lee (born 2003, likes Rap) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- I'm digging the beat of this song! I can feel the energy of the abracadabra and it's so awesome. This reminds me of ceremonial rap. It's like you're chanting magic with the music. 

3.What Tina Smith (born 1996, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- This song is gorgeous! The lyrics are so mysterious but beautiful at the same time. The mix of the good fairy and witch princess is so captivating, the abracadabra truly makes me feel electricity. 

4. What Bobby Reynolds (born 1995, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- This is quite interesting! Abracadabra brings me to a whole new world of mystery. There's a lot of imagery with the good fairy, witch princess, rabbit in a hat, and salt for wishes. Definitely brings a rock n' roll vibe to the song.

5. What Rachel Johnson (born 1992, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- This is a perfect wish granting anthem! I love the mix of the good fairy and witch princess to bring out the power of the abracadabra. It's like inviting enchantment and magic into your life, I'm definitely feeling this vibes!


6. What Shawn Johnson (born 1991, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- What a cool song! I love the underlying power of the abracadabra behind the good fairy and witch princess. This song captures so many magical elements and brings forth a rocking free spirit vibe. 

7. What Jake White (born 1989, likes Pop) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- This song is hypnotizing! It's like opening a doorway with the abracadabra into a mystical realm. The good fairy and witch princess are so intriguing, I can feel the power of the song perfectly.

8.What Cyrus McCall (born 1988, likes Rap) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- This song is sick! I can feel the power and energy of the abracadabra with the clever lyrics. It's like you're chanting magic with the good fairy and witch princess in the mix. This one's definitely fire! 

9. What Kelly Taylor (born 1987, likes Rock) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- This is so epic! I love the mix of the good fairy, witch princess, and abracadabra. It's like a story within the lyrics taking you to a wondrous place. The rock power behind the song is undeniable. 

10. What Mike Richards (born 1977, likes Heavy Metal) would think while hearing the song with these lyrics.
- This is powerful! I love the intensity of the abracadabra behind the good fairy and witch princess. The heavy metal vibe comes through with the rabbit in the hat and salt for wishes, this song is an absolute blast!

Scene 1:
Hey there, good fairy waving her wand, 
Or princess with her magical brew, 
No rabbit's hat or pinch of salt, 
Just hoping my wish will come true one day.

Chorus: 
Abracadabra, this should do me some good, 
Abracadabraz, start loving me like it should.

Scene 2:
Eating birds' claws, lizards' stew, 
Reading spells this evening too, 
Seeing light from the crystal ball, 
Dreams ruined, that's no good at all. 

Bridge:
Scrutinizing my own grimoire, 
A book for the youth's lore, 
Kissing the last frog to get one woman's form.
